notesStmt.note: Some leaves fully laminated. Infills and patches.
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1; ruled lines: 16; written lines: 16; Uniform layout. Catchwords on every page. Ruled with mastara. Larger square initial words. Hebrew foliation added by a later hand.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Oriental semi-cursive and square scripts of the 16th to 17th century.

binding.p: BM in-house. Spine: 'Piyyutim. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Oriental 5400.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Purchased by the British Museum on 12 July 1898 from S. Raffalovich: inscribed, folio [143v] (fse001v).
